cs.NE, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SD

The paper discusses a differential model inspired by neuron interactions in the primary visual cortex (V1) and applied to image processing problems. This suggests that the paper could belong to the sub-categories of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also mentions the use of mathematical equations and numerical tests, which could indicate a connection to the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper discusses geometric-optical illusions, which could suggest a connection to the sub-category of cs.SD (Sound and Image Processing).
